Adam is General Manager of IntalioWorks, which includes the BPMS, Jetty and Cometd offerings from Intalio, and
operates with a commercial open source model in 15 countries around the world. Previously, he was CEO of Webtide,
which focused on services for Jetty and Cometd, where he helped bring the Jetty project to the Eclipse Foundation
Runtime project. Previously, he was a co-founder of Gluecode Software, a pioneer in commercial open source
offerings, which was acquired by IBM, where he lead worldwide sales for the group. 